Based on the architectural blueprints and design principles established for the **Codessa Platform**, the multi-agent-factory module represents the core control plane responsible for transforming probabilistic LLM workflows into a governed, deterministic, and cryptographically auditable multi-agent runtime.
Rather than relying on traditional, non-deterministic agent orchestration frameworks (which suffer from state drift, loose execution loops, and race conditions), this module functions as an execution kernel compiler and state manager.
### 1. Architectural Core Analysis
The multi-agent-factory must be analyzed through its three foundational design constraints: **Deterministic Execution**, **Epistemic Governance**, and **Resource Isolation**.
